    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i know, i know. people always say \"it gets better\" or \"reach out,\" but that just feels like more work, you know? more effort to maintain a life that doesn't even feel real. i look at the crowd and i just see a bunch of people who would keep eating their lunch and walking to work if i just... wasn't there. it's almost comforting to think that there's no real impact one person makes. if i just let go, it wouldn't even be a tragedy, just a quiet exit. it seems more logical than fighting to stay visible for a world that doesn't care.",
